LAGOS – Sadiq Umar and Wil­liam Troost-Ekong scored in the second half to hand Super Eagles of Nigeria a 2-0 win against the Wild Dogs of Guinea Bissau in their last group D match of the ongo­ing Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) in Cameroon. After several missed chances in the first half, the Super Eagles changed the game in the second half and immediately took the fight to their opponents. Almeria of Spain strik­er, Sadiq scored in the 56th minute off a Kelechi Ihe­anacho laid through ball. National Assembly Re-Amends Electoral Act Amendment Bill Tinubu’s Associates Split Over Osinbajo’s Alleged Presidential… The dangling striker who was ineffective during the first half, tapped in for the Super Eagles opener be­fore he was subbed off for Peter Olayinka Defender, William Troost- Ekong put the game beyond the Wild Dogs after he tapped into the net a rebound from winger, Moses Simon. Simon had made a dot­ting run inside the box, dribbled past four defend­ers only to see his shot bounce off the bar before Troost-Ekong tapped in. A lengthy Video Assis­tant Referee check later confirmed that the Watford FC defender was onside be­fore he scored The victory ensures that coach Augustine Eguavoen has preserved his record as the only Nigeria coach to win all three group match­es in the tournament. He did it in 2006 and repeated it in 2021 edition. POLL Nigeria will remain in Garoua for their Round of 16 clash next week. In the other group D match, Egypt defeated Sudan 1-0 to confirm their passage into the last 16.